Grenade Attack Kills 11 in Pakistani Cinema
Pakistani officials say at least 11 people were killed after assailants threw grenades into a crowded movie theater in the city of Peshawar.At least 20 others were injured.No one has claimed responsibility for the attack -- the second of its kind in the area this month. This latest attack comes amid peace talks between the government and the Pakistani Taliban aimed at ending a nearly decade long insurgency in Pakistan's northwest.